    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-09-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-09-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="157"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d157">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Her Majesty’s Foreign Office</persName> to <persName
                        type="to">Laird Brothers</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign Office,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-09-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 4, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Gentlemen:</hi> Earl Russell has been led to understand
                    that you have intimated that, while you were not in a position to volunteer
                    information respecting the iron-clad vessels lately launched and now being
                    fitted out at your yard, you would readily furnish information upon an official
                    application in writing being made to you for it.</p>
                <p>Under these circumstances, Lord Russell has instructed me to request you to
                    inform him, with as little delay as possible, on whose account, and with what
                    destination, these vessels have been built.</p>
                <p>I am, gentlemen, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>A. H. LAYARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Messrs. <hi rend="smallcaps">Laird</hi> &amp; Co., <hi rend="italic"
                            >Birkenhead.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
